def: A tasteless, yellow, crystalline substance, obtained from thegentian; -- called also gentianin.
A low-lying meadow by the side of a river. [Prov. Eng. & Scot.]On a haugh or level plain, near to a royal borough. Sir W. Scott.
Fit to be deputed; suitable to act as a deputy. Carlyle.
The process of converting, or of being converted, into afossil.
One who treats of the origin of the universe; one versed incosmogony.
To make a parenthesis of; to include within parentheticalmarks. Lowell.
A mounted peddler of fish; -- called also jouster. [Obs.]Carew.
A stand of wood or iron, with hooks or pegs upon which to hanghats, etc.
Having no jointed legs; pertaining to Anarthropoda.
